{title:"See the sights of Tokyo in this 150-gigapixel panorama", author:"Aaron Souppouris", content:"<div class="article-body instapaper_body entry-content"> <p>If you've spent any length of time on the internet, chances are you've seen a multi-gigapixel image before. Giant composite photographs, often made up of thousands upon thousands of individual high-resolution shots, have documented an<a href="http://www.theverge.com/2012/11/30/3709676/charles-babbage-difference-engine-gigapixel-images%20early%20mechanical%20computers">early mechanical computer</a>, President<a href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/1/22/3904808/where-in-the-world-is-beyonce">Obama's inauguration</a>, a<a href="http://www.theverge.com/2012/8/7/3225635/virtual-nanoscopy-281-gigapixel-embryo-image">zebrafish embryo</a>, and even<a href="http://www.theverge.com/2012/8/13/3240137/360-degree-mars-panorama-curiosity-rover/in/2986732">the surface of Mars</a>. This latest shot, created by 360 Cities founder Jeffery Martin, gives a highly-detailed view of Tokyo from the observation deck of Tokyo Tower.</p> <!-- extended entry --><hr class="widget_boundry_marker hidden page_break"> <p><iframe style="height: 400px; width: 560px; border: 0px;" src="http://360gigapixels.com/tokyo-tower-panorama-photo/embed.html"></iframe></p> <p>The 150-gigapixel panorama was created from 10,000 individual photos captured using Martin's Canon EOS 7D DSLR camera and an<a target="_blank" href="http://www.dr-clauss.de/en/foto-studiotechnik-3/rodeon-vr-head-series">Clauss Rodeon panorama head</a>. It took two days to shoot all the necessary photographs, and twelve weeks to stitch together the panorama using an ultra-high power computer. According to 360 cities, a printed version of the panorama would be 328 feet long and 164 feet tall â€” almost the same size as a football field. You can explore the shot in the viewer above, but for a full-resolution version, and<a target="_blank" href="http://360gigapixels.com/tokyo-gigapixel-roppongi-hills-mori-tower/">an additional 45-gigapixel image</a>, head to 360 Cities.</p> <div class="article-meta clearfix"><ul class="simplelist sourcelist clearfix"> <li class="via clearfix"> <strong>Via</strong><span><a href="http://news.cnet.com/8301-17938_105-57596789-1/zoom-around-tokyo-in-an-epic-150-gigapixel-image/">CNET</a></span> </li> <li class="source clearfix"> <strong>Source</strong><span><a href="http://360gigapixels.com/tokyo-tower-panorama-photo/">360 Cities</a><a href="http://360gigapixels.com/tokyo-tower-panorama-photo/assets/pdf/360cities-Tokyo-Tower-Gigapixel-Press-Release.pdf">(PR)</a></span> </li> <li class="tags clearfix"> <strong>Related Items</strong><span><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/japan">japan</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/tokyo">tokyo</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/panorama">panorama</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/gigapixel">gigapixel</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/360-cities">360 cities</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/tokyo-tower">tokyo tower</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/clauss-rodeon">clauss rodeon</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/tag/jeffery-martin">jeffery martin</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/products/eos-7d/1208">EOS 7D</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/products/brands/canon/14">Canon</a><a href="http://www.theverge.com/products/categories/dslrs/10">DSLRs</a></span> </li> </ul></div> </div>"}